Abuja, NIGERIA:  Professor Femi Soyinka, president of the International Conference on AIDS and Sexually Transmitted infections in Africa, speaks 04 December 2005 on the efforts being made to curtail the spread of HIV and AIDS in family circles during a briefing in Abuja to flag off the 14th international conference on the epidemic in Africa. African and international health experts gathered in the Nigerian capital Abuja 04 December to launch a major conference on how best to break the HIV/AIDS virus' deadly grip on the continent and care for its 24 million victims.      AFP PHOTO   PIUS UTOMI EKPEI   (Photo credit should read PIUS UTOMI EKPEI/AFP via Getty Images)
        
 

